Now, let's continue with Green Globe.

60
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Green Globe is an international organization dedicated to sustainability certification in the tourism and hospitality industry.

61
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:42,000
Its main goal is to promote responsible practices toward the environment, society, and the economy,

62
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:46,000
helping businesses in the sector operate more sustainably.

63
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,000
What does Green Globe handle?

64
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:57,000
Certifying the sustainability of hotels, resorts, convention centers, travel agencies, tourist attractions, and destinations.

65
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:07,000
Auditing environmental, social, and economic practices to ensure companies meet certain international sustainability criteria.

66
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:18,000
Providing continuous improvement tools such as performance reports and recommendations to reduce environmental impact and improve sustainable management.

67
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:22,000
What requirements must a company meet to join Green Globe?

68
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:33,000
To obtain Green Globe certification, a company must meet more than 50% of the 44 basic criteria grouped into four main areas.

69
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Environmental sustainability.

70
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:47,000
This refers to efficient use of energy and water, waste management and recycling, protection of biodiversity and local ecosystems, and reduction of carbon emissions.

71
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,000
Sustainable management.

72
00:11:49,000 --> 00:12:02,000
This involves sustainability policies integrated into business strategy, staff training on environmental and social issues, evaluation and control of operational impact.

73
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,000
Social responsibility.

74
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,000
Respect for local culture and community.

75
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Inclusion of the community in decision-making and business benefits.

76
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,000
Fair and safe working conditions.

77
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,000
Cultural and economic aspects.

78
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Promotion of local culture and heritage.

79
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,000
Support for local products and suppliers.

80
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,000
Economic transparency.

81
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:29,000
The certification process starts with membership in Green Globe.

82
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,000
An initial assessment.

83
